  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: School - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_school">School</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_educational_establishment">Educational Establishment</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_school">School</xref>
 provides education for children of statutory 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_school">School</xref>
 age (5-16 years old) although they may provide education outside these ages as well, i.e. nurseries and sixth form.        </p>
    <p>
An up to date list of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_school">Schools</xref>
 in England can be found on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_department_for_education">Department for Education</xref>
 part of the gov.uk website at: 
              <xref href="https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/" scope="external" format="html">Get information about schools</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
